{"type":"message","id":"3a0edab1","parentId":"2b5eca43","timestamp":"2026-04-15T04:08:01.261Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Memory retrieval is disabled. Let me compare current state against what I know from the last report (which was at 04:02 UTC from the sessions history):\n\nFrom the last report (04:02 UTC):\n- cron:e7885813 — no longer active, cycle ended and not restarted\n- agent:master-orchestrator:main — ended normally at ~03:25 UTC\n- Lead direct (telegram:direct:6053576134) — 6 child subagents spawned and active\n- Active sessions: 3 (QLHV 5p ✅ DTLX 5p ✅ Lead direct 🔄)\n\n\n- Blockers: DTLX Telegram group failed and two orphaned cron jobs\n\nNow checking what's actually running at 04:07 UTC: the DTLX 5p cron is active, the QLHV Telegram group session ended, and the QLHV 5p cron is still running with three child sessions spawned.\n\nThe lead direct session has 6 child subagents still active and waiting for user input, while the main orchestrator is done and the DTLX group session remains failed. The main orchestrator has been inactive since around 03:25 UTC.\n\nComparing this to the last report at 04:02 UTC, I notice the DTLX 5p cron is still running, but the Agent Status cron session has disappeared.  The Lead direct session with its 6 children is still active but now has a queued message from the user asking about configuration references. The QLHV 5p session has spawned new child agents. The critical issue is that the Agent Status cron that's been failing repeatedly has now stopped entirely—that's a meaningful change I need to track. The DTLX group is still failing as expected. Looking at the queued messages, there's a user question about hiding configuration files from agent references that needs attention. I'm checking if the Agent Status cron session has actually ended or just completed its current cycle, but the session list shows it's no longer active — the last completed run was around 02:28 UTC, and the previous report confirmed it was gone, so it appears to be stopped.\n\nNow I'm comparing the active sessions from 04:07 against what was reported at 04:02: the DTLX 5p cron is still running, but the Agent Status session is gone, and the Lead direct session remains active with 6 children.\n\nThe Lead session has a queued message from the user about hiding configuration files, which suggests it's still engaged. I need to decide whether to report this as a state change or stay silent—the Agent Status session ending could be normal, but combined with the queued message in the Lead session, there's enough activity to justify reporting the current state to the group.","thinkingSignature":"adf1e88f54e4ab43271600a0dd293cbda165dae4da10a83cceaa51ac07924cd2"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing against last known report (04:02 UTC):\n\n**Changes:**\n- ❌ **Agent Status cron (cron:e7885813)** — gone. Was ending/not restarting at 04:02, now confirmed absent from session list. No longer cycling.\n- 🔄 **Lead direct** (`telegram:direct:6053576134`) — 6 child subagents still active, user has queued message pending (about hiding config references from agents).\n- 🔄 **QLHV 5p** (`cron:ed2d0b5d`) — 3 child planner sessions still active.\n\n**Stable:**\n- DTLX 5p ✅ | DTLX group ❌ (failed, unchanged) | main ❌ (done, unchanged).\n\n🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | 04:07 UTC 15 Apr\n\nChanges detected:\n• ❌ Agent Status cron (`cron:e7885813`) — confirmed gone from session list. Recurring abort cycle has ended.\n• 🔄 Lead direct (`telegram:direct:6053576134`) — 6 child agents still active, user message queued (question about hiding config/SOUL references from agents)\n• 🔄 QLHV 5p Monitor — 3 planner child sessions still running\n\nPipeline: ⚠️ DEGRADED\n• Active sessions: 3 (QLHV 5p ✅ DTLX 5p ✅ Lead direct 🔄)\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• Blockers: ⚠️ DTLX Telegram group failed (~1h) | Agent Status cron ended | ⚠️ cron:ac986a8d orphan | ⚠️ cron:b653a6c0 orphan\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":9232,"output":941,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":429,"totalTokens":24546,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776226060398,"responseId":"062e420d926d7a1912c42a87fb3048b2"}}
